Innings break Australia make an impressive score in the end. They were 5 for 140 but Maxwell and Carey shared a 134-run stand to dig them out of a hole. Maxwell had a lot of luck but he played some superb shots as well. He ended up two short of a century. He now has five scores in the 90s in ODI cricket but just one century. Carey did a great job in support. Pakistan will rue several missed chances and Shinwari's wicket off a no-ball. They could have been chasing less than 250. Now 278 looks a big ask on this slow low surface. Liam Brickhill will be back in about 30 minutes to take you through the start of the chase.
